# Cross-origin isolation for SharedArrayBuffer (Whisper WASM threading).
# `credentialless` (vs require-corp) still yields crossOriginIsolated on
# Chrome/Edge — the only browsers Whisper runs on — without forcing every
# cross-origin resource (transformers.js CDN, HuggingFace weights) to send CORP.
#
# Scoped to the Whisper transcriber ONLY. Applying `COOP: same-origin` to the
# lobby/room strips `window.opener`, which breaks Clerk's OAuth sign-in popups.
# The lobby/room need no SharedArrayBuffer; only the Whisper transcriber does.
# Both the pretty URL (/transcribe) and the raw asset (/transcribe.html) are
# listed because the assets layer serves the extensionless path directly.
/transcribe
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: credentialless
/transcribe.html
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: credentialless
